When {{IPA|/-a/}} / {{IPA|/-u/}} / {{IPA|/-inː/}} is suffixed to a noun ending in {{IPA|/a/}} or {{IPA|/u/}} epenthetic {{IPA|/j/}} is inserted, e.g. {{IPA|/tabardaja/}} ('this pack-saddle').

Other deictic suffixes: {{IPA|/-dːɣ/}} ('this'), {{IPA|/-nːa/}} ('that'), e.g. {{IPA|/tadːartdːɣ/}} ('this house'), {{IPA|/tadːartnːa/}} ('that house').

== Verbs ==

Verbs are marked for [[grammatical tense|tense]], [[grammatical aspect|aspect]], [[grammatical mode|mode]], [[voice (grammar)|voice]], and [[grammatical polarity|polarity]], and agree with the [[grammatical number|number]], [[grammatical person|person]], and [[grammatical gender|gender]] of the subject.

'''Verb framing'''

[[Satellite framing]] is accomplished with the proximate affix<ref group="nb">These are "moveable affixes", like the object pronominal affixes, and whether they are prefixed or suffixed depends on environmental factors</ref> /d/ (/dː/ in AS) and remote /nː/, e.g. /dːu/ 'to go' yields /i-dːa/ 'he went', /i-dːa-d/ 'he came', /i-dːa-nː/ 'he went there' (in AS the verb /rˠaħ/ 'to go' is used instead)<ref>{{Harvcoltxt|Abdel-Massih|1971b|pp=154–155, 216}}</ref>

'''Voice'''

Derived verb stems may be made from basic verb stems to create causatives, reciprocals, recipro-causatives, passives, or habituals.<ref>{{Harvcoltxt|Abdel-Massih|1971b|p=155}}</ref>

Causatives are derived from unaugmented stems with the prefix /s(ː)-/.<ref group="nb">This is a feature of many [[Afro-Asiatic languages]]</ref><ref>{{Harvcoltxt|Abdel-Massih|1971b|p=179}}</ref>
:/ħudr/ 'bend' > /'''s'''ħudr/

Habituals are derived from unaugmented and reciprocal/recipro-causative stems with the prefix /tː-/ (sometimes with internal change), from causatives by an infixed vowel, and from passives by an optional infixed vowel:<ref>{{Harvcoltxt|Abdel-Massih|1971b|pp=176, 179, 181–182}}</ref>
/fa/ 'yawn' > /tːfa/
:(/ħudr/ 'bend' >) /sħudr/ > /sħud'''u'''r/
:(/ʕum/ 'swim' > /mːsʕum/ >) /'''tː'''mːsʕum/
:(/bdr/ 'mention' > /tːubdr/ >) /tːubd'''a'''r/

Reciprocals are formed with the prefix /m(ː)-/, and recipro-causatives with /-m(ː)s-/, sometimes with internal change.<ref>{{Harvcoltxt|Abdel-Massih|1971b|pp=180–181}}</ref>
: /sal/ 'ask' > /'''mː'''sal/

Passives are formed with the prefix /tːu-/:<ref>{{Harvcoltxt|Abdel-Massih|1971b|pp=181–182}}</ref>
/ħnːa/ 'pity' > /'''tːu'''ħnːa/

'''Tense, mode, and subject'''

{{IPA|/ad-/}} marks future tense, {{IPA|/is-/}} marks interrogative mode, and {{IPA|/ur-/}} marks negative mode.

Pronominal complement markers cliticize to the verb, with the indirect object preceding the direct object, e.g. /izn-as-t/ "he sold it to him".<ref>[http://www.univie.ac.at/linguistics/tagungen/phon02/wopal/abstracts/wopal_louali_and_philippson.pdf Vowel apophony and underlying segments in Siwa Berber (Egypt)]</ref>
