'''Ili Turki''' is a [[Turkic languages|Turkic language]] spoken primarily in [[China]]. There were approximately 120 speakers of this language in 1982.

==Classification==
Ili Turki appears to belong to the [[Chagatay Turkic languages|Chagatay group]] of Turkic languages, although it exhibits a number of features that suggest a [[Kypchak languages|Kipchak]] [[substratum]].<ref>{{cite journal
 | author = Zhào Xiāngrú and Reinhard F. Hahn
 | year = 1989
 | title = The Ili Turk People and Their Language
 | journal = [[Central Asiatic Journal]]
 | volume = 33
 | issue = 3/4
 | pages = 261–285
 }}
</ref>
<ref>{{cite journal
 | author = Reinhard F. Hahn
 | year = 1991
 | title = An Annotated Sample of Ili Turki
 | journal = Acta Orientalia Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae 
 | volume = 45
 | issue = 1
 | pages = 31–53
 }}
</ref>

