{{Infobox language |name=Remo |nativename=Môa Remo |states=[[Peru]] |region=[[Môa River]] |ethnicity=[[Remo people|Remo]] |extinct=? |ref=e10<!--"no contact but some recent leads" in Ethn.08--> |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Panoan languages|Panoan]] |fam2=Mainline Panoan |fam3=Nawa |fam4=Headwaters group |iso3=rem |glotto=remo1248 |glottorefname=Remo }}
'''Remo''' (Rheno) is an [[extinct language|extinct]] indigenous language once spoken along the [[Môa River]] of [[Amazonas Region|Amazonas]], [[Peru]], one of several [[Panoan languages]] to go by that name. It was similar to [[Amawaka language|Amawaka]].
